records.addlTxt:
Defendant Andrew J Ohlsson in court with attorney Michael J Steinle.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for sentencing hearing.
Christine O., victim's mother presented statements to the court.
Kevin O., victim's father presented statements to the court.
Lance O., defendant's brother spoke on defendant's behalf.
Jeff J., friend of defendant, spoke on defendant's behalf.

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

TERM OF PROBATION: 2 and 1/2  YEARS WITHHELD;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Any and all sex offender treatment that's deemed appropriate by Agent;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  victim whatsoever by any method or medium;
*Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
*Register as a sex offender for the period of probation only.
*Use or access of computer equipment is to be determined by agent; 
*No use or possession of any video or recording devices. 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of probation;

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 to be paid as a condition of probation;

CONDITION TIME: 120 days with huber (non-working hours) commencing June 6, 2016 by 6:00 p.m. Release for treatment, counseling, work and school. Last 60 days stayed to be used at agent's discretion. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
